        "title": "The Outlook (Gresham)",
        "content": "{{Short description|Newspaper in Oregon, U.S.}}\n{{Infobox newspaper\n| name               = The Outlook\n| image              = The Outlook (Gresham OR) front page 2018.jpg\n| type               = [[Biweekly newspaper]]\n| foundation         = 1911\n| owners             = [[Pamplin Media Group]]\n| maneditor          = Steve Brown\n| circulation        = 9,068\n| circulation_date   = 2022\n| circulation_ref    = <ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-10-19 |title=Pamplin Media Group: Media Kit 2022|url=https://bloximages.chicago2.vip.townnews.com/portlandtribune.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/1/d3/1d3da40a-5099-11ed-8c18-6797ea52fec9/63517f7ec4dd5.pdf.pdf |access-date=2023-04-18}}</ref>\n| website            = {{URL|theoutlookonline.com}}\n| publishing_city    = [[Gresham, Oregon]], U.S.\n| language           = English\n}}\n'''''The Outlook''''' is a newspaper published in [[Gresham, Oregon]], a suburb of [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]] in the U.S. state of [[Oregon]]. It was founded in 1911,<ref>Terry, John (July 19, 2011). [http://www.oregonlive.com/century/1910_newsreel.html A Place Called Eden]. ''[[The Oregonian]]''. Retrieved July 31, 2012.</ref><ref name=bluebook>[https://sos.oregon.gov/blue-book/Pages/cultural/media-newspapers.aspx Newspapers Published in Oregon] ''[[Oregon Blue Book]]''. Retrieved July 31, 2012.</ref> and is owned by the [[Pamplin Media Group]].\n\n== History ==\nThe newspaper was named the '''''Gresham Outlook''''' from 1911 to 1991 and was published by H. L. St. Clair,<ref name=loc1>{{cite web | title=About the Gresham Outlook | work = [[Chronicling America]]| publisher=[[Library of Congress]] | url=\nhttp://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn97071044/ | access-date=July 31, 2012}}</ref> who incorporated the business as the Outlook Publishing Company in 1917. The paper was renamed simply ''The Outlook'' in 1991.<ref name=loc2>{{cite web | title=About The Outlook (Gresham, Or.) | work = Chronicling America| publisher=Library of Congress | url=http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn97071045/ | access-date=July 31, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe newspaper was purchased in 1960 by Lee Irwin and Walt Taylor,<ref name=\"paper sold\">\"Paper Sold At Gresham\" (March 31, 1960). ''The Oregonian'', p. 5.</ref> and Irwin was its publisher from 1960 to 1982.<ref name=\"Irwin wraps\">McCowan, Karen (September 8, 1982). \"Gresham Outlook publisher retires: Irwin wraps up 50-year career\". ''[[The Oregonian]]'', p. ME7.</ref> He was followed by Robert Caldwell for a relatively short period, with Steven J. Clark being named publisher effective April 4, 1983.<ref>\"Lake Oswego newsman to be publisher of Gresham Outlook\" (March 17, 1983). ''The Oregonian'' (South Metro edition), p. C1.</ref>\n\nIrwin and Taylor sold the ''Gresham Outlook'' in 1977 to the Democrat-Herald Publishing Co., which published the ''[[Albany Democrat-Herald]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |date=February 10, 1977 |title=Publisher buys 4 weeklies |work=Statesman Journal |pages=37}}</ref> [[Capital Cities Communications|Capital Cities]] purchased the company in 1980,<ref>{{Cite news |date=July 14, 1980 |title=Paper sale should be final today |work=Albany Democrat-Herald |pages=3}}</ref> which itself was acquired by [[The Walt Disney Company]] in 1995.<ref name=\"Disney acquisition of Capital Cities/ABC Inc.\">{{cite news |author=Geraldine Fabrikant |date=5 January 1996 |title=THE MEDIA BUSINESS;Disney and ABC Shareholders Solidly Approve Merger Deal |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/01/05/business/the-media-business-disney-and-abc-shareholders-solidly-approve-merger-deal.html |access-date=July 8, 2013 |work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> Disney sold its Oregon newspapers to [[Lee Enterprises]] in 1997,<ref>{{Cite news |date=September 9, 1997 |title=Lee Enterprises closes purchase of Oregon newspapers from ABC |work=The Oregonian |pages=45}}</ref> and three years later Lee sold ''The Outlook'' to [[Robert B. Pamplin, Jr.]] in 2000.<ref name=\"millionaire\">Tomlinson, Stuart (November 12, 2000). \"Millionaire buys four more news operations\". ''The Sunday Oregonian'', p. B8.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{official website|http://www.theoutlookonline.com}}\n\n{{Oregon Newspaper Publishers Association}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Outlook (Gresham), The}}\n[[Category:Gresham, Oregon]]\n[[Category:1911 establishments in Oregon]]\n[[Category:Newspapers published by Pamplin Media Group]]\n[[Category:Oregon Newspaper Publishers Association]]\n[[Category:Newspapers established in 1911]]\n[[Category:Biweekly newspapers published in the United States]]\n\n\n{{Oregon-newspaper-stub}}"
