        "title": "Saltstraumen Church",
        "content": "{{short description|Church in Nordland, Norway}}\n{{Infobox church\n|name                   = Saltstraumen Church\n|fullname               = Saltstraumen kirke\n|former name            = \n|image                  = Saltstraumen kirke.jpg\n|caption                = View of the church\n|website                = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|67.2335095|14.62547690|region:NO_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n|location               = [[Bodø Municipality]], [[Nordland]]\n|country                = [[Norway]]\n|churchmanship          = [[Evangelical Lutheran]]\n|denomination           = [[Church of Norway]]\n|diocese                = [[Diocese of Sør-Hålogaland|Sør-Hålogaland]]\n|deanery                = [[Bodø domprosti]] \n|parish                 = Saltstraumen\n|status                 = [[Parish church]]\n|functional status      = Active\n|founded date           = 1886\n|consecrated date       = 1886\n|completed date         = {{Start date and age|p=y|1886}}\n|closed date            = \n|events                 = Moved in 1900\n|architect              = J. E. Olsen\n|architectural type     = [[Churches in Norway#Floor plan|Long church]]\n|style                  = \n|materials              = Wood\n|capacity               = 370\n|embedded = {{Norwegian Cultural Heritage Site\n|embed                  = yes\n|Type                   = Church\n|Status                 = Not protected\n|ID                     = 85365\n}} }}\n\n'''Saltstraumen Church''' ({{langx|no|Saltstraumen kirke}}) is a [[parish church]] of the [[Church of Norway]] in [[Bodø Municipality]] in [[Nordland]] county, [[Norway]]. It is located in the village of [[Saltstraumen]]. It is one of the two churches for the Saltstraumen [[parish]] which is part of the [[Bodø domprosti]] ([[deanery]]) in the [[Diocese of Sør-Hålogaland]]. The white, wooden church was built in a [[Churches in Norway#Floor plan|long church]] style in 1886 using plans drawn up by the [[architect]] J. E. Olsen. The church seats about 370 people.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Saltstraumen kirke |url=https://kirkesok.no/kirke/180400301 |access-date=2018-11-01 |publisher=Kirkesøk: Kirkebyggdatabasen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Oversikt over Nåværende Kirker |url=http://www.kirkekonsulenten.no/kirker.htm |access-date=2018-11-01 |publisher=KirkeKonsulenten.no |language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe church was originally built in 1886. Around 1900, the building was moved about {{convert|300|m}} to the northwest from its original location due to soil instability. The cemetery remained at the original site.<ref name=\"LH\">{{Cite web |title=Saltstraumen kirke |url=https://lokalhistoriewiki.no/wiki/Saltstraumen_kirke |access-date=2021-04-01 |website=LokalHistorieWiki.no |language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n\n==Media gallery==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\">\nSaltstraumen kirke 2.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje 2011.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje tårnet.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje.jpg|\nVed Bodø omegn - no-nb digifoto 20151009 00031 NB MIT FNR 05127.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje galleriet.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje inni 1.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje inni.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje koret.jpg|\nSaltstraumen kyrkje preikestol.jpg|\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of churches in Sør-Hålogaland]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Churches in Bodø}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2021}}\n\n[[Category:Churches in Bodø]]\n[[Category:Churches in Nordland]]\n[[Category:Wooden churches in Norway]]\n[[Category:19th-century Church of Norway church buildings]]\n[[Category:Churches completed in 1886]]\n[[Category:1886 establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:Long churches in Norway]]"
