        "title": "Kazi Ebadoth Hossain",
        "content": "{{Short description|Bangladeshi judge}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| name                = \n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = bn\n| office              = Justice of the [[High Court Division, Supreme Court of Bangladesh|High Court Division of Bangladesh]]\n| term_start          =\n| birth_date          = \n| nationality         = Bangladeshi\n| profession          = [[Judge]]\n| alma_mater          = \n}}\n'''Kazi Ebadoth Hossain''' is a Justice of the [[High Court Division]] of the [[Bangladesh Supreme Court]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=11 High Court benches formed to hear death reference cases {{!}} News |url=https://www.bssnews.net/news/49229 |access-date=2023-08-09 |website=BSS}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nHossain was born on 1 October 1969.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web |title=Home : Supreme Court of Bangladesh |url=https://www.supremecourt.gov.bd/web/indexn.php?page=judges.php&menu=11&div_id=2&lang= |website=supremecourt.gov.bd |access-date=9 August 2023}}</ref> He did his bachelor's and master's in law from the [[University of Dhaka]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Career==\nHossain became a lawyer in the district court in 1993 and the High Court Division in 2003.<ref name=\":0\" /> He was a member of the Dhaka University LLM Lawyers' Association.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2008-07-18 |title=DU LLM Lawyers' Assoc executives |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-46289 |access-date=2023-08-09 |website=The Daily Star |language=en}}</ref> \n\nOn 21 October 2019, Hossain was appointed an additional judge of the High Court Division.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn 19 October 2021, Hossain was made a permanent judge of the High Court Division by President [[Mohammad Abdul Hamid]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-10-19 |title=Nine new High Court judges take oath |url=https://www.tbsnews.net/bangladesh/court/nine-new-high-court-judges-take-oath-318085 |access-date=2023-08-09 |website=The Business Standard |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2022, Hossain and Justice [[Md Rezaul Hasan]] confirmed the death penalty in the  Mymensingh double murder.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-03 |title=Death penalty a proper punishment for brutal killing: HC on 2014 Mymensingh double murder |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/crime-justice/news/death-penalty-proper-punishment-brutal-killing-hc-2014-mymensingh-double-murder-2997151 |access-date=2023-08-09 |website=The Daily Star |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2023, Hossain and Justice [[Zubayer Rahman Chowdhury]] in a verdict declared [[Jatiya Muktijoddhya Council|Jatiya Muktijoddha Council]] has no authority to cancel the names of \"Freedom Fighter\" from gazette notification.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-06 |title=Muktijoddha Council: 'It cannot exclude freedom fighters' names from gazette' |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news/bangladesh/news/muktijoddha-council-it-cannot-exclude-freedom-fighters-names-gazette-3213651 |access-date=2023-08-09 |website=The Daily Star |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hossain, Kazi Ebadoth}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:University of Dhaka alumni]]\n[[Category:Supreme Court of Bangladesh justices]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi lawyers]]"
