        "title": "Bangladesh Volleyball Federation",
        "content": "{{Infobox organization\n|name         = Bangladesh Volleyball Federation\n|image         = \n|image_border = \n|size         = \n|alt          = \n|caption      = \n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|malt         = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1973\n|extinction   = \n|type         = \n|status       = \n|purpose      = \n|headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n|location     = \n|coords       = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template -->\n|region_served = Bangladesh\n|members  = \n|language     = Bengali\n|leader_title = \n|leader_name  = \n|main_organ   = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations = \n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers =\n|budget       = \n|website      = \n|remarks      =\n}}\nThe '''Bangladesh Volleyball Federation''' is the national federation for volleyball and is responsible for governing the sport in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite news |title=Victory Day Volleyball begins Sunday |url=https://unb.com.bd/category/Sports/victory-day-volleyball-begins-sunday/38898 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=[[United News of Bangladesh]] |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Volleyball federation suspend all activities|url=https://dailyasianage.com/news/224020/volleyball-federation--suspend-all-activities |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=[[The Asian Age]] |language=en}}</ref> Mr. Md. Atiqul Islam is the president and Ashiqur Rahman Miku is the general secretary of the federation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bangamata Volleyball: Bangladesh concedes 0-3 sets defeat against Maldives |url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/post/223182 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=[[The Independent (Bangladesh)]] |location=[[Dhaka]]}}</ref>\n\nThe federation also runs many national and international tournaments.\n\n== National Tournaments ==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Tournament\n!Year\n!Sponsor\n!Winner\n!Runner's up\n|-\n|Victory Day\n|2022\n|Walton\n|\n|\n|-\n|Independence Day\n|2022\n|Walton\n|\n|\n|}\n\n== International Tournaments ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Tournaments\n!Year\n!Winner\n!Runner's up\n|-\n!Bangabandhu Volleyball Championship \n!2019\n!\n!\n|-\n!Bangamata Volleyball Championship\n!2019\n!\n!\n|-\n|}\n!Bangabandhu Volleyball Championship \n!2022\n!\n!\n|-\n\n==History==\nBangladesh Volleyball Federation was established in 1973 by the [[Government of Bangladesh]]. Since its founding, the federation has held national volleyball tournaments for both, men and women.<ref name=\"pedia\">{{cite web |last1=Faroqi |first1=Gofran |title=Volleyball |url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Volleyball |website=[[Banglapedia]] |accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{National members of the International Federation of Volleyball}}\n{{Sports governing bodies in Bangladesh}}\n[[Category:Volleyball in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:National members of the Asian Volleyball Confederation]]\n[[Category:1973 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Sports organizations established in 1973]]\n[[Category:Sports governing bodies in Bangladesh|Volleyball]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Dhaka]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-org-stub}}"
