        "content": "{{short description|Bosnian musician}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Dušan Vranić\n| image           =\n| image_size      =\n| caption         =\n| birth_date      =\n| birth_place     = [[Sarajevo]], [[Socialist Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina|SR Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| alias           = {{flatlist|\n* Duco \n* Dutso \n* V. Eliane\n}}\n| origin          =\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* Rock\n* [[pop rock]]\n* [[garage rock]]\n* [[alternative rock]]\n* [[gypsy style]]\n* [[electronic music|electronic]]\n}}\n| occupation      = Musician\n| instrument      = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* keyboards\n* drums\n* percussion\n* [[sitar]]\n}}\n| years_active    = <!-- 1990–present -->\n| label           =\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Darko Rundek]]\n* [[Zabranjeno Pušenje]]\n* [[Sikter]]\n* [[Stéphane Sanseverino]]\n* [[R.E.M.]]\n}}\n| website         = \n}}\n'''Dušan Vranić''', known by his nickname '''Duco''', is a Bosnian musician who is a member of the [[Darko Rundek]]'s band. Formerly, he was a member of a Bosnian [[garage rock]] band [[Zabranjeno Pušenje]]. \n\n== Life and career ==\nVranić was born and raised in [[Sarajevo]], [[Socialist Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina|SR Bosnia and Herzegovina]].<ref name=\"rundek\">{{cite web |title=Cargo: Dušan Vranić – Duco |url=http://www.darko-rundek.com/det.php?movid=41&groid=11 |website=darko-rundek.com |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref> He is a [[self-taught]] musician.\n\nIn 1994, Vranić came to France with a pop-rock band Overdream.<ref name=\"rundek\"/> Next to him, the band members are [[Samir Ćeramida]], [[Đani Pervan]], [[Sejo Kovo]], and Boris Bačvić.<ref>{{cite web |title=Overdream |url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/2184181-Overdream-4 |website=discogs.com |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref> The band released their only studio album in 1996.\n\nIn 1996, Vranić accompanied [[Sejo Sexon]] and [[Elvis J. Kurtović]], with whom he restarted band [[Zabranjeno Pušenje]], disbanded in the early 1990s.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kako je i kad nastalo Zabranjeno Pušenje? |url=https://www.jabuka.tv/kako-je-i-kad-nastalo-zabranjeno-pusenje/ |website=jabuka.tv |accessdate=16 December 2019|language=bs}}</ref> He performed on their fifth studio album, ''[[Fildžan viška]]'', which was released in 1997.<ref>{{cite web |title=Zabranjeno Pušenje – Fildžan Viška |url=https://www.discogs.com/Zabranjeno-Pu%C5%A1enje-Fild%C5%BEan-Vi%C5%A1ka/release/2711197 |website=discogs.com |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nAmerican singer-songwriter [[Michael Stipe]] hired Vranić and Đani Pervan to make [[remix]]es of two songs, \"I've Been High\" and \"Beachball\", from [[R.E.M.]]'s album ''[[Reveal (R.E.M. album)|Reveal]]'' (2001).<ref>{{cite web |title=Pariška družina Darka Rundeka |url=http://arhiva.nacional.hr/clanak/13299/pariska-druzina-darka-rundeka |website=nacional.hr |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref> The two of them did mentioned remixes under pseudonym Chef.<ref name=\"rundek\"/>\n\nIn 2001, Vranić accompanied [[Darko Rundek]] with whom he performed on his studio album ''Ruke'' (2002).<ref>{{cite web |title=Darko Rundek – Ruke |url=https://www.discogs.com/Darko-Rundek-Ruke/release/2982361 |website=discogs.com |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref> Later, Vranić and Rundek founded Rundek Cargo Orkestar, as well as Rundek Cargo Trio. Three musicians, Vranić, Rundek, and a Swiss violinist Isabel Catala released two studio albums as Rundek Cargo Trio; ''Plavi avion'' (2010) and ''Mostovi'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web |title=Rundek Cargo Trio |url=https://www.menart.hr/glazba/hr/rundek-cargo-trio |website=menart.hr |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n;Overdream\n* ''Overdream'' (1996)\n\n;Zabranjeno pušenje\n* ''[[Fildžan viška]]'' (1997)\n\n;Darko Rundek & Cargo Orkestar\n* ''Ruke'' (2002)\n* ''Zagrebačka Magla: Plava turneja 2003 Live'' (2004)\n* ''Mhm A-ha Oh Yeah Da-Da!'' (2006)\n* ''Live u Domu omladine'' (2008)\n\n;Rundek Cargo Trio\n* ''Plavi Avion'' (2010)\n* ''Mostovi'' (2015)\n* ''Generacija '68 Soundtrack'' (2016)<ref>{{cite web |title=Generation of 68 |url=https://www.havc.hr/eng/croatian-film/croatian-film-catalogue/generation-of-68 |website=havc.hr |accessdate=25 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.discogs.com/artist/857579-Du%C5%A1an-Vrani%C4%87 Dušan Vranić] on [[Discogs]]\n\n{{Sikter}}\n{{Zabranjeno Pušenje}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vranic, Dusan}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Bosnia and Herzegovina male singers]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina rock musicians]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina expatriates in France]]\n[[Category:21st-century multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Sarajevo]]\n[[Category:Zabranjeno Pušenje members]]\n[[Category:21st-century Bosnia and Herzegovina male singers]]"
