        "title": "Debora Diniz",
        "content": "{{Short description|Brazilian anthropologist}}\n[[File:Debora Diniz 2019.jpg|thumb|Debora Diniz interviewed on ''[[The Laura Flanders Show]]'' in 2019]]\n'''Debora Diniz Rodrigues''' (known as '''Debora Diniz'''), is an anthropologist and law professor at the [[University of Brasília]], and a co-founder and researcher at Anis: Institute for Bioethics. She is also a researcher, writer and documentary filmmaker. Her research projects focus on bioethics, feminism, human rights and health. She was a visiting researcher at the [[University of Leeds]], the [[University of Michigan]], the [[University of Toronto]], among other institutions.<ref name=\"lattes\">{{Cite web\n |url= http://buscatextual.cnpq.br/buscatextual/visualizacv.jsp?id=K4728397Y1\n |title= Currículo do Sistema de Currículos Lattes (Debora Diniz)\n |access-date= 2016-08-19\n |archive-date= 2009-10-06\n |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20091006130924/http://buscatextual.cnpq.br/buscatextual/visualizacv.jsp?id=K4728397Y1\n |url-status= live\n }}</ref><ref name=\"epoca\">{{cite web\n |url= http://revistaepoca.globo.com/Epoca/0,6993,EPT757558-1666-1,00.html\n |title= Entrevista\n |access-date= 2016-08-19\n |archive-date= 2017-01-12\n |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170112223144/http://revistaepoca.globo.com/Epoca/0,6993,EPT757558-1666-1,00.html\n |url-status= live\n }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web\n |url=https://www.iwhc.org/boards/debora-diniz/\n |title=Debora Diniz\n |access-date=2016-08-19\n |archive-date=2017-11-01\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171101165636/https://iwhc.org/boards/debora-diniz/\n |url-status=live\n }}</ref>\n\nBy 2016, Diniz had received about 90 awards, including scientific and academic awards for her films at festivals, including the Fred L. Soper Award for Excellence in Public Health Literature, the Pan American Health Organization, in 2012, for the publication of her National Abortion Survey.<ref>{{Cite web\n |url= http://www.forumplp.org.br/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1712:debora-diniz-ganha-premio-de-direitos-humanos-da-universidade-de-sao-paulo&catid=1:recente&Itemid=18 |archive-url= https://archive.today/20121128230910/http://www.forumplp.org.br/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1712:debora-diniz-ganha-premio-de-direitos-humanos-da-universidade-de-sao-paulo&catid=1:recente&Itemid=18 |url-status= dead |archive-date= 2012-11-28 |title= Debora Diniz ganha prêmio de Direitos Humanos da Universidade de São Paulo }}</ref> In 2020 she was honored with the [[Dan David Prize]].<ref>[https://www.dandavidprize.org/laureates/2020 Dan David Prize 2020]</ref>\n\nHer research found that one in five Brazilian women had an abortion by age 40.<ref>{{Cite web\n |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/08/opinion/the-zika-virus-and-brazilian-womens-right-to-choose.html?_r=0\n |title= The Zika Virus and Brazilian Women's Right to Choose\n |work= The New York Times\n |access-date= 2017-03-01\n |archive-date= 2017-10-20\n |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20171020121900/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/02/08/opinion/the-zika-virus-and-brazilian-womens-right-to-choose.html?_r=0\n |url-status= live\n }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 she published ''Zika: From the Brazilian Backlands to Global Threat'' (Zed Books).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Krauss|first=Amy|date=2018|title=Zika: From the Brazilian Backlands to Global Threat by Debora Diniz (review)|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/article/713866|journal=Luso-Brazilian Review|language=en|volume=55|issue=2|pages=E13–E15|doi=10.3368/lbr.55.2.E13|s2cid=149936281|issn=1548-9957}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Stolow|first1=Jeni|last2=Castro|first2=Arachu|volume=32|issue=4|date=December 2018|title=Zika: From the Brazilian Backlands to Global Threat|url=http://medanthroquarterly.org/article/zika-from-the-brazilian-backlands-to-global-threat/|access-date=2021-02-26|journal=Medical Anthropology Quarterly|publisher=Society for Medical Anthropology|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=McLemee|first=Scott|date=September 13, 2017|title=Review of Debora Diniz's 'Zika: From the Brazilian Backlands to Global Threat'|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/views/2017/09/13/review-debora-dinizs-zika-brazilian-backlands-global-threat|url-status=live|access-date=2021-02-26|website=Inside Higher Ed|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170914073251/https://www.insidehighered.com/views/2017/09/13/review-debora-dinizs-zika-brazilian-backlands-global-threat |archive-date=2017-09-14 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Howells|first=Michaela|date=2018|title=Zika: From the Brazilian Backlands to Global Threat Debora Diniz Zed Publishing. 192 pp, $16.50 (Paperback), $15.68 ebook (kindle)|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/ajhb.23081|journal=American Journal of Human Biology|language=en|volume=30|issue=2|pages=e23081|doi=10.1002/ajhb.23081|issn=1520-6300}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2022 she was amongst 151 international feminists signing ''Feminist Resistance Against War: A Manifesto'', in solidarity with the [[Feminist Anti-War Resistance]] initiated by Russian feminists after the [[Russian invasion of Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Feminist Resistance Against War: A Manifesto | date=17 March 2022 | website=Specter Journal | url=https://spectrejournal.com/feminist-resistance-against-war/ | access-date=31 March 2022 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diniz, Debora}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Academic staff of the University of Brasília]]\n[[Category:University of Michigan people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian exiles]]"
