        "title": "Max Sirena",
        "content": "{{short description|Italian sailor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = \n| image          = \n| imagesize      =\n| caption        = \n| fullname       = \n| nicknames      =\n| nationality    = {{ITA}}\n| classes        = [[AC75]] ([[2021 Prada Cup]])\n| club           = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1971|12|4|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Rimini]], [[Italy]]\n| death_date     =  \n| death_place    = \n| height         = \n| weight         = \n| retired        = \n| show-medals    = yes\n| medaltemplates =\n}}\n'''Massimiliano \"Max\" Sirena''' (born 4 December 1971 in [[Rimini]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.sportmagazine.it/altri-sport/2021/01/29/max-sirena-chi-e/ | title=Chi è Max Sirena, lo Skipper e Team Director di Luna Rossa | date=29 January 2021 | publisher=SportMagazine | accessdate=14 February 2021}}</ref>) is an Italian [[sailor (sport)|sailor]] who has competed in multiple [[America's Cup]]s.\n\n==Biography==\nSirena sailed with [[Luna Rossa Challenge]] in their [[2000 Louis Vuitton Cup|2000]], [[2000 Louis Vuitton Cup|2003]] and [[2007 Louis Vuitton Cup]] campaigns as a mid-bowman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lunarossachallenge.com/en/team/108_Massimiliano-Sirena|title=Massimiliano Sirena – Luna Rossa|first=Luna|last=Rossa|website=www.lunarossachallenge.com|accessdate=19 July 2017}}</ref> Sirena was the wing mast manager for [[Oracle Racing]] when they won the [[2010 America's Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lunarossachallenge.com/en/team/100_Max-Sirena|title=Max Sirena – Luna Rossa|first=Luna|last=Rossa|website=www.lunarossachallenge.com|accessdate=19 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nSirena skippered [[Luna Rossa Challenge]] in the [[2013 Louis Vuitton Cup]]. The team won the [[2011 Extreme Sailing Series]]. After Luna Rossa withdrew from the [[2017 America's Cup]], Sirena joined [[Team New Zealand]] in a management role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/other-sports/72767358/team-new-zealand-sign-italian-americas-cup-winner-max-sirena|title=Team New Zealand sign Italian America's Cup winner Max Sirena|website=Stuff|accessdate=19 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sailingscuttlebutt.com/2015/10/06/americas-cup-max-sirena-trading-places/|title=America's Cup: Max Sirena Trading Places >> Scuttlebutt Sailing News|date=6 October 2015|website=Scuttlebutt Sailing News|accessdate=19 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newshub.co.nz/home/sport/2015/10/luna-rossa-skipper-max-sirena-joins-team-nz.html|title=Luna Rossa skipper Max Sirena joins Team New Zealand|date=10 July 2015|publisher=|accessdate=19 July 2017|via=www.newshub.co.nz}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Italy at the America's Cup]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.lunarossachallenge.com/it/team/185_Max-Sirena Max Sirena] at [[Luna Rossa Challenge]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sirena, Max}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:2000 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:2003 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:2007 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:2013 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rimini]]\n[[Category:Luna Rossa Challenge sailors]]\n[[Category:Oracle Racing sailors]]\n[[Category:Team New Zealand sailors]]\n[[Category:Extreme Sailing Series sailors]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:2021 America's Cup sailors]]\n\n\n{{Italy-yachtracing-bio-stub}}"
