        "title": "Christophorus Records",
        "content": "{{Short description|German classical music label}}\n{{Infobox record label <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Music -->\n| name        = Christophorus Records\n| image       = <!-- logo, such as \"LABEL-LOGO.jpg\" -->\n| image_size  = <!-- size -->\n| image_alt   = <!-- WP:ALT text describing the image -->\n| caption     = <!-- a caption for the image -->\n| parent      = <!-- parent company, such as \"[[Warner Music Group]]\" -->\n| founded     = 1939\n| founder     = <!-- name of founders, separate with commas or <br /> -->\n| defunct     = <!-- year the label dissolved, such as {{end date|1990}} -->\n| status      = <!-- leave blank unless \"Inactive\" -->\n| distributor = <!-- distributors, separate with commas or <br /> -->\n| genre       = Classical\n| country     = Germany\n| location    = Freiburg im Breisgau\n| website     = <!-- such as \"{{URL|www.atlanticrecords.com}}\" -->\n}}\n\n'''Christophorus Records''' is a German classical music label based originally in [[Freiburg im Breisgau]] specializing in [[Catholic]] church and [[early music]].<ref>[http://www.christophorus-records.de/v2.php Official Homepage]</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe history of the Herder family in publishing in Freiburg goes back to Bartholomä Herder (1774–1839) ''Fürstbischöflicher Hofbuchhändler und Hofbuchdrucker'' in 1801. The publishing house of Herder still exists.<ref>[http://www.herder.de/ Website of Herder]</ref> The [[Christianity|Christian]] book publishers Christophorus-Verlag Herder KG. was founded by Hermann Herder und Dr. Josef Knecht in 1935 as a passive resistance to developments in [[religion in Nazi Germany]].<ref>[http://christophorus-verlag.de Website of Christophorus-Verlag]</ref><ref>''Im Dienst am Buch: Bartholomä Herder, Benjamin Herder, Hermann Herder'' Albert Maria Weiss, Engelbert Krebs, Julius Dorneich – 1951 FÜNFZEHNTES KAPITEL – DER CHRISTOPHORUS-VERLAG HERDER – Entstehung und Aufgaben Als Tochtergesellschaft des Verlages Herder wurde am St. Josephstag 1935 der Christophorus-Verlag Herder KG. gegründet. Hermann Herder und Dr. Josef Knecht ..\"</ref><ref>Dokumentation deutschsprachiger Verlage. 14. Ausgabe. Dagmar Olzog, Johann Hacker – 2001</ref><ref>Bartholomä, Benjamin und Hermann Herder\" (1951); „Der Katholizismus in Deutschland und der Verlag Herder\" (1951)</ref><ref>„Bartholomä Herder. Verleger – Drucker – Buchhändler\" (durchgesehene Neuauflage 2001)</ref><ref>„Der Verlag Herder 1801–2001.</ref> Christophorus Schallplatten began as a part of the picture book division of Christophorus Verlag in 1939. The record label is now distributed by Musicontact GmbH, [[Heidelberg]].\n\n==Artists==\nAmong the artists who have regularly recorded for the label are [[Ensemble für frühe Musik Augsburg]], [[Johann Rosenmüller Ensemble]], [[Spielleyt]], [[Stimmwerck]], and [[Don Cossacks Choir Russia]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official|http://www.christophorus-records.de/v2.php}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Classical music record labels]]"
