        "title": "Gmina Wielichowo",
        "content": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Gmina Wielichowo\n| other_name = Wielichowo Commune\n| settlement_type = [[Gmina]]\n| image_flag =\n| image_shield = POL Wielichowo COA.svg\n| image_map =\n| coordinates = {{coord|52|7|8|N|16|20|58|E|region:PL|display=inline,title}}\n| coor_pinpoint = Wielichowo\n| subdivision_type = Country\n| subdivision_name = {{POL}}\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Voivodeships of Poland|Voivodeship]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Greater Poland Voivodeship|Greater Poland]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[Powiat|County]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Grodzisk Wielkopolski]]\n| seat = [[Wielichowo]]\n| total_type = Total\n| area_total_km2 = 107.43\n<!--\n| population_as_of = 2006\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_urban = 1765\n| population_rural = 5129\n| population_total = 6867\n-->\n| population_total = 6894\n| population_as_of = 2011<ref>[http://stat.gov.pl/en/topics/population/population/ Demographic Yearbook of Poland 2012]</ref> \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_urban = 1757\n| population_rural = 5110\n| website = {{URL|http://www.wielichowo.pl}}\n}}__NOTOC__\n'''Gmina Wielichowo''' is an urban-rural [[gmina]] (administrative district) in [[Grodzisk Wielkopolski County]], [[Greater Poland Voivodeship]], in west-central [[Poland]]. Its seat is the town of [[Wielichowo]], which lies approximately {{convert|13|km|mi|0}} south of [[Grodzisk Wielkopolski]] and {{convert|50|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-west of the regional capital [[Poznań]].\n\nThe gmina covers an area of {{convert|107.43|km2|sqmi|1}}, and as of 2006 its total population is 6,894 (out of which the population of Wielichowo amounts to 1,765, and the population of the rural part of the gmina is 5,129).\n\n==Villages==\nApart from the town of Wielichowo, Gmina Wielichowo contains the villages and settlements of [[Augustowo, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Augustowo]], [[Borek, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Borek]], [[Celinki]], [[Dębsko, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Dębsko]], [[Gradowice]], [[Helenopol, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Helenopol]], [[Łubnica, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Łubnica]], [[Mokrzec, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Mokrzec]], [[Pawłówko, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Pawłówko]], [[Piotrowo Wielkie]], [[Prochy, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Prochy]], [[Pruszkowo, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Pruszkowo]], [[Reńsko, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Reńsko]], [[Śniaty, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Śniaty]], [[Trzcinica, Grodzisk Wielkopolski County|Trzcinica]], [[Wielichowo-Wieś]], [[Wilkowo Polskie]], [[Zielęcin, Greater Poland Voivodeship|Zielęcin]] and [[Ziemin]].\n\n==Neighbouring gminas==\nGmina Wielichowo is bordered by the gminas of [[Gmina Kamieniec|Kamieniec]], [[Gmina Przemęt|Przemęt]], [[Gmina Rakoniewice|Rakoniewice]] and [[Gmina Śmigiel|Śmigiel]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|1}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071227152516/http://www.stat.gov.pl/gus/45_655_PLK_HTML.htm Polish official population figures 2006]\n\n{{Gmina Wielichowo}}\n{{Grodzisk Wielkopolski County}}\n\n[[Category:Gminas in Greater Poland Voivodeship|Wielichowo]]\n[[Category:Grodzisk Wielkopolski County]]"
