        "title": "Voici",
        "content": "{{Short description|French women's magazine}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2021}}\n{{Infobox magazine|\n  title          = Voici |\n  image_file     = Voici.jpg |\n  image_size     = 191px |\n  image_caption  =  ''Voici'' magazine cover, from the week of 1 May 2007.|\n  editor         =  Hedi Dahmani|\n  editor_title   = |\n  frequency      = Weekly |\n  circulation    = 408,120 (2010)  |\n  category       = Celebrity and [[Women's magazine]]|\n  company        = [[Vivendi]]|\n  publisher      = [[Prisma Presse]] |\n  founded        = {{start date and age|1987}}  |\n  firstdate      =  |\n  country        = [[France]] |\n  based          = [[Paris]] |\n  language       = [[French language|French]] |\n  website        = [http://www.voici.fr/ ''Voici''] |\n  issn           = 0245-5803|}}\n'''''Voici''''' is a [[French language]] weekly [[celebrity]] and [[gossip magazine]]<ref>{{Cite book|author=Sophie Marnette|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lyCufkCSi-IC&pg=PA288|page=288|title=Speech and Thought Presentation in French: Concepts and Strategies|date=2005|publisher=John Benjamins Publishing|isbn=978-90-272-5376-7}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|author1=Jamil Dakhlia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0i5U6VE59F0C&pg=PA37|page=37|title=Politique people|author2=Jocelyne Dakhlia|date=2008|publisher=Editions Bréal|isbn=978-2-7495-0521-3|language=fr}}</ref> published in [[Paris]], [[France]].\n\n==History and profile==\n''Voici'' was founded in 1987.<ref name=haf>{{cite journal|author=Helena Hafstrand|title=Consumer Magazines in Transition|journal=The Journal of Media Economics|date=1995|volume=8|issue=1|url=https://doi.org/10.1207/s15327736me0801_1|doi=10.1207/s15327736me0801_1}}</ref><ref name=ham>{{cite web|title=Monday November 18 2002: the weekly magazine Voici at 15!|url=http://www.guj.de/en/press/press-releases/monday-november-18-2002-the-weekly-magazine-voici-at-15/|work=G+J|access-date=1 March 2015|location=Hamburg|date=17 November 2002}}</ref> The magazine is published on a weekly basis<ref name=fip/> and is based in Paris.<ref name=ham/> The weekly is owned by the [[Germany|German]] [[media company]], [[Bertelsmann]]/[[Gruner + Jahr]].<ref>{{cite book|author1=Anthony Weymouth|author2=Bernard Lamizet|title=Markets and Myths: Forces For Change In the European Media|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E8O3AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA128|date=3 June 2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-88970-0|page=128}}</ref> The publisher is the Prisma Presse,<ref name=fip/> a subsidiary of Gruner+Jahr.<ref>{{cite web|title=Interview with Rolf Heinz, Président of Prisma Media|url=http://www.bertelsmann.com/news-and-media/news/interview-with-rolf-heinz-president-of-prisma-media.jsp|work=Bertelsmann|access-date=17 April 2015|location=Paris|date=27 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n''Voici'' claims the title of best selling French celebrity magazine, and second or third most widely read French women's magazine.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.prismapub.com/plain/content/download/232/1318/file/Fiche_int_Voici.pdf|title=Voici: N°1 people magazine & The women's sweet spot|url-status= dead|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20070927211923/http://www.prismapub.com/plain/content/download/232/1318/file/Fiche_int_Voici.pdf|archive-date=27 September 2007|df=dmy-all}}&nbsp;{{small|(734&nbsp;KB)}}, readership profile, ''Prisma Presse''. Retrieved 1 May 2007.</ref> It includes beauty, fashion, health, society and entertainment sections.\n\n==Circulation==\n''Voici'' had a circulation of 602,000 copies in 1991.<ref name=haf/> Its circulation was 576,000 copies in 1998.<ref>{{cite web|author=François Dalbard-Martin|title=RPC, Buying Habits and the Time Factor in Media Planning|url=http://www.pdrf.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/612.pdf|work=World Wide Readership Symposia|access-date=1 March 2015|format=Conference paper|date=2001}}</ref> In 2000 the circulation of the magazine was 514,180 copies and it was 522,042 copies in 2001.<ref name=ham/>\n\nThe circulation of ''Voici'' was 493,000 copies during the 2007–2008 period.<ref>{{cite web|author=Anne Austin |display-authors=etal|title=Western Europe Market & Media Fact|url=http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact_2008/Western%20Europe%20Market%20&%20MediaFact%202008.pdf|work=Zenith Optimedia|access-date=8 April 2015|date=2008}}</ref> The weekly was the third best-selling celebrity magazine in France with a circulation of 408,000 copies in 2009.<ref>{{cite book|author=Raymond Kuhn|title=The Media In Contemporary France|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3oVTBgAAQBAJ&pg=RA4-PA9|date=1 March 2011|publisher=McGraw-Hill Education (UK)|isbn=978-0-335-23622-0|page=9}}</ref> Its circulation was 408,120 copies in 2010.<ref name=fip>{{cite web|title=World Magazine Trends 2010/2011|url=http://www.revistas-ari.com/attachments/209_WMT_2010_2011_Europe.pdf|work=FIPP|access-date=5 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.voici.fr/ Official website]\n\n{{Vivendi}}\n\n[[Category:1987 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:Celebrity magazines]]\n[[Category:French-language magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1987]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Paris]]\n[[Category:News magazines published in France]]\n[[Category:Weekly magazines published in France]]\n[[Category:Women's magazines published in France]]\n[[Category:Prisma Media]]"
