        "title": "Kolchugino, Vladimir Oblast",
        "content": "{{Short description|Town in Vladimir Oblast, Russia}}\n{{Other places3|Kolchugino}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox Russian town\n|en_name=Kolchugino\n|ru_name=Кольчугино\n|image_skyline=Kolchugino-now4.jpg\n|image_caption=View of Kolchugino\n|coordinates = {{coord|56|19|N|39|22|E|display=inline,title}}\n|map_label_position=right\n|image_flag=Flag of Kolchugino (Vladimir oblast).png\n|flag_caption\n|image_coa=Coat of Arms of Kolchugino (Vladimir oblast).png\n|coa_caption=\n|anthem\n|anthem_ref\n|holiday\n|holiday_ref\n|federal_subject=[[Vladimir Oblast]]\n|federal_subject_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirO_admlist\" />\n|adm_data_as_of=September 2013\n|adm_district_jur=[[Kolchuginsky District]]\n|adm_district_jur_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirO_admlist\" />\n|adm_ctr_of=Kolchuginsky District\n|adm_ctr_of_ref=<ref name=\"OKATO\" />\n|inhabloc_cat=Town\n|inhabloc_cat_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirO_admlist\" />\n|inhabloc_type=\n|inhabloc_type_ref=\n|mun_data_as_of=July 2013\n|mun_district_jur=Kolchuginsky Municipal District\n|mun_district_jur_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirOKolchuginskyD_mun\" />\n|urban_settlement_jur=Kolchugino Urban Settlement\n|urban_settlement_jur_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirOKolchuginskyD_mun\" />\n|mun_admctr_of1=Kolchuginsky Municipal District\n|mun_admctr_of1_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirOKolchuginskyD_mun\" />\n|mun_admctr_of2=Kolchugino Urban Settlement\n|mun_admctr_of2_ref=<ref name=\"VladimirOKolchuginskyD_mun\" />\n|leader_title\n|leader_title_ref\n|leader_name\n|leader_name_ref\n|representative_body\n|representative_body_ref\n<!----STATISTICS---->\n|area_of_what\n|area_as_of\n|area_km2\n|area_km2_ref\n|pop_2010census=45776\n|pop_2010census_ref=<ref name=\"2010Census\">{{ru-pop-ref|2010Census}}</ref>\n|pop_latest=\n|pop_latest_date=\n|pop_latest_ref=\n<!----HISTORY---->\n|established_date=1871\n|established_title=\n|established_date_ref=\n|current_cat_date=1931\n|current_cat_date_ref\n|prev_name1\n|prev_name1_date\n|prev_name1_ref\n<!----MISCELLANEA---->\n|postal_codes=\n|postal_codes_ref\n|dialing_codes=\n|dialing_codes_ref\n|website=http://www.gorod.kolchadm.ru/\n|website_ref\n|commonscat=Kolchugino\n|date=October 2010\n}}\n'''Kolchugino''' ({{langx|ru|Кольчу́гино}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|town]] and the [[administrative center]] of [[Kolchuginsky District]] in [[Vladimir Oblast]], [[Russia]], located on the [[Peksha River]] ([[Klyazma River|Klyazma]]'s [[tributary]]) some {{convert|74|km|sp=us}} northwest of [[Vladimir, Russia|Vladimir]], the administrative center of the [[oblast]]. Population: {{ru-census|p2021=39410|p2010=45,776|p2002=47,059|p1989=45,601}}\n\n==History==\nKolchugino was founded in 1871 as a settlement next to [[copper]]-[[annealing (metallurgy)|annealing]] and [[wire]]-producing plants belonging to a [[Moscow|Muscovite]] merchant A.&nbsp;G.&nbsp;Kolchugin (hence, the name Kolchugino).{{citation needed|date=October 2013}} It was granted town status in 1931.{{citation needed|date=October 2013}}\n\n==Administrative and municipal status==\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Administrative divisions|framework of administrative divisions]], Kolchugino serves as the [[administrative center]] of [[Kolchuginsky District]],<ref name=\"OKATO\">{{OKATO reference|17 240}}</ref> to which it is directly subordinated.<ref name=\"VladimirO_admlist\">Resolution #433</ref> As a [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal division]], the [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|town]] of Kolchugino, together with nine rural localities in Kolchuginsky District, is incorporated within Kolchuginsky Municipal District as '''Kolchugino Urban Settlement'''.<ref name=\"VladimirOKolchuginskyD_mun\">Law #64-OZ</ref>\n\n==Economy==\n[[File:Kolch samovar.jpg|thumb|left|[[Samovar]] and ''[[podstakannik]]'' made by Kolchugino plant]]\n[[File:Kolch podstakannik1.jpg|thumb|left|''[[Podstakannik]]s'' made by Kolchugino plant]]\n\nThe town is well known for [[Kolchug-Mizar|its tableware plant]], founded by Alexander Kolchugin. Most of [[podstakannik|Russian tea glass-holders]] were produced in Kolchugino.\n\n[[Types of business entity in Russia|ZAO]] [[Kolchugtsvetmet]], also located in Kolchugino and founded in 1871, is the largest manufacturer of non-ferrous mill products in the [[Commonwealth of Independent States]].\n\n==References==\n===Notes===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|vla|adm|list}}\n*{{RussiaAdmMunRef|vla|mun|list|kolchuginsky}}\n\n{{Vladimir Oblast}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Vladimir Oblast]]\n[[Category:Vladimir Governorate]]"
