        "title": "Kohleria",
        "content": "{{Short description|Genus of flowering plants}}\n{{more footnotes needed|date=April 2021}}\n{{Automatic taxobox\n| image = Gesneriaceae - Kohleria amabilis var. bogotensis.JPG\n| image_caption = [[Kohleria amabilis|''Kohleria amabilis'' var. ''bogotensis'']]\n| taxon = Kohleria\n| authority = [[Eduard August von Regel|Regel]]<ref name=POWO_17084-1/>\n| synonyms =\n  {{Genus list\n  |Brachyloma|Hanst.\n  |Calycostemma|Hanst.\n  |Campanea|Decne.\n  |Capanea|Decne. ex Planch.\n  |Cryptoloma|Hanst.\n  |Giesleria|Regel\n  |Isoloma|Decne.\n  |Sciadocalyx|Regel\n  |Synepilaena|Baill.\n  |Tydaea|Decne.\n  }}\n| synonyms_ref = <ref name=POWO_17084-1/>\n| subdivision_ranks = Species\n| subdivision = [[#Species|See text]].\n}}\n\n'''''Kohleria''''' is a [[New World]] [[genus]] of the [[flowering plant]] family [[Gesneriaceae]]. The plants are generally tropical herbs or subshrubs with velvety stems and foliage and brightly colored flowers with spots or markings in contrasting colors. They are rhizomatous and commonly include a period of dormancy in their growth cycle. The genus was revised in 1992 and was then recognized as having 19 species distributed in [[Central America]] and [[South America]]. [[Phylogenetics|phylogenetic]] in 2005 indicated that the epiphytic genus ''Capanea'' is derived from within ''Kohleria'', and the two species of ''Capanea'' were subsequently transferred to ''Kohleria''. The genus ''[[Pearcea]]'' is closely related.\n\nBecause of their colorful and exotically patterned flowers, as well as a general interest in the many tropical flowering plants that were being introduced from the Americas, kohlerias were very popular in [[England]] and [[Europe]] in the 19th century. Many species and [[Hybrid (biology)|hybrids]] were lavishly illustrated in horticultural magazines such as Curtis's Botanical Magazine under the discarded or erroneous names of ''[[Achimenes]]'', ''[[Gesneria]]'', ''[[Isotoma (plant)|Isoloma]]'', ''[[Sciadocalyx]]'', and ''[[Tydaea]]''.  These species and hybrids almost entirely disappeared in the early 20th century, and [[plant breeders]] have only recently begun to work extensively with this genus again.\n\nSeveral species are widespread, variable, weedy, and tend to hybridize in the wild, and numerous names have been described that are synonyms of other species or are hybrid taxa.\n\n== Species ==\n{{As of|2024|August}}, [[Plants of the World Online]] accepted the following species:<ref name=\"POWO_17084-1\">{{cite web |title=''Kohleria'' Regel |work=Plants of the World Online |publisher=Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew|url=https://powo.science.kew.org/taxon/urn:lsid:ipni.org:names:17084-1 |access-date=9 August 2024}}</ref>\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n*''[[Kohleria affinis]]'' <small>(Fritsch) Roalson & Boggan</small> (syn. ''Capanea affinis'')\n*''[[Kohleria allenii]]'' <small>Standl. & L.O.Williams</small>\n*''[[Kohleria amabilis]]'' <small>(Planch. & Linden) Fritsch</small>\n*''[[Kohleria andina]]'' {{small|(Fritsch) J.L.Clark & L.Jost}}\n*''[[Kohleria anisophylla]]'' <small>(Fritsch) Wiehler</small>\n*''[[Kohleria bella]]'' <small>C.V.Morton</small>\n*''[[Kohleria diastemoides]]'' <small>L.P.Kvist & L.E.Skog</small>\n*[[Kohleria × gigantea|''Kohleria'' × ''gigantea'']] <small>(Planch.) Fritsch</small>\n*''[[Kohleria grandiflora]]'' <small>L.P.Kvist & L.E.Skog</small>\n*''[[Kohleria hirsuta]]'' <small>(Kunth) Regel</small>\n*''[[Kohleria hondensis]]'' <small>(Kunth) Regel</small>\n*''[[Kohleria huilensis]]'' {{small|Arango-Gómez, Clavijo & Zuluaga}}\n*''[[Kohleria hypertrichosa]]'' <small>J.L.Clark & L.E.Skog</small>\n*''[[Kohleria inaequalis]]'' <small>(Benth.) Wiehler</small>\n*''[[Kohleria longicalyx]]'' <small>L.P.Kvist & L.E.Skog</small>\n*''[[Kohleria neglecta]]'' <small>L.P.Kvist & L.E.Skog</small>\n*''[[Kohleria peruviana]]'' <small>Fritsch</small>\n*''[[Kohleria rugata]]'' <small>(Scheidw.) L.P.Kvist & L.E.Skog</small>\n*''[[Kohleria spicata]]'' <small>(Kunth) Oerst.</small>\n*''[[Kohleria stuebeliana]]'' <small>Fritsch</small>\n*''[[Kohleria tigridia]]'' <small>(Ohlend.) Roalson & Boggan</small> (syn. ''Capanea grandiflora'')\n*''[[Kohleria trianae]]'' <small>(Regel) Hanst.</small>\n*''[[Kohleria tubiflora]]'' <small>(Cav.) Hanst.</small>\n*''[[Kohleria villosa]]'' <small>(Fritsch) Wiehler</small>\n*''[[Kohleria warszewiczii]]'' <small>(Regel) Hanst.</small> – [[Award of Garden Merit|AGM]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Cultivation==\nTheir showy flowers and ease of culture have made them popular with growers of indoor [[houseplant]]s. Numerous species and hybrids are now in cultivation, some with patterned or variegated foliage as well as vivid flowers. They are easily propagated by both stem cuttings and division of the rhizomes.\n\n==References and external links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n*Kvist, L.P. & L.E. Skog.  1992. Revision of ''Kohleria'' (Gesneriaceae). ''Smithsonian Contributions to Botany'' 79: 1-83, [https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/6988/scb-0079.pdf pdf].\n*{{citation |jstor=25065368 |author=Roalson, E.H. |author2=J.K. Boggan, L.E., Skog |author3=E.A. Zimmer |name-list-style=amp |date=2005 |title=Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic data sets |journal=Taxon |volume=54 |issue=2 |pages=389–410 |doi=10.2307/25065368}}\n*{{cite journal |author1=Roalson E.H. |author2=Boggan J.K. |author3=Skog L.E. | year = 2005 | title = Reorganization of tribal and generic boundaries in the Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae: Gesnerioideae) and the description of a new tribe in the Gesnerioideae, Sphaerorrhizeae | journal = Selbyana | volume = 25 | issue = 2| pages = 225–238 }}\n*[http://www.botanik.univie.ac.at/morphology/genera_gesneriaceae/genera/Kohleria.htm ''Kohleria'']{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} from [https://archive.today/20121128223257/http://www.botanik.univie.ac.at/morphology/genera_gesneriaceae/index.htm The Genera of Gesneriaceae]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051118181814/http://gesneriads.ca/genkohle.htm ''Kohleria'' and ''Koellikeria''] from the [http://gesneriads.ca Gesneriad Reference Web]\n*[http://www.egradini.ro/articole/kohleria.html ''Kohleria'' ] from the [http://www.egradini.ro eGradini.ro - Romanian Gardening Website]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2585772}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Gesnerioideae]]\n[[Category:Gesneriaceae genera]]\n[[Category:Neotropical realm flora]]\n[[Category:Taxa described in 1847]]\n[[Category:Taxa named by Eduard August von Regel]]"
