        "title": "Count Screwloose",
        "content": "{{Short description|1929–1935 American comic strip}}\n'''Count Screwloose''' is a character in the comic strip ''Count Screwloose from Tooloose'' by [[Milt Gross]], introduced on February 17, 1929. The count is portrayed as a mentally ill man who frequently leaves Nuttycrest Sanitarium, the [[insane asylum]] where he resides, to go out into the rest of the world. There he often meets people who act crazier than he did and thus he always goes back, telling his dog Iggy: \"Iggy, keep an eye on me\", which became a national [[catchphrase]] at the time. The series was discontinued in 1935.<ref name=\"Markstein\">{{cite web |url=http://www.toonopedia.com/screwloo.htm |title=Count Screwloose of Tooloose  |last=Markstein |first=Don |date=2006 |website=[[Don Markstein's Toonopedia]] |publisher= |access-date=December 22, 2020 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nIn 1937, the comic strip was adapted into a short-lived cartoon series by [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer cartoon studio|Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]. Two cartoons were released in 1939.<ref name=\"Markstein\"></ref>\n\n==History==\nThe [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer cartoon studio]] brought in established newspaper cartoonist [[Milt Gross]] in an attempt to both bolster the [[The Captain and the Kids (film series)|Captain and the Kids]] product and create original properties for MGM, but his tenure at the studio was short-lived. Gross managed to complete two cartoons, ''Jitterbug Follies'' and ''Wanted: No Master'', with his characters Count Screwloose of Tooloose and J.R. the Wonder Dog.\n* ''Jitterbug Follies''\n* ''Wanted: No Master''\n\n==References==\n{{portal|Comics}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:American comic strips]]\n[[Category:1929 comics debuts]]\n[[Category:1935 comics endings]]\n[[Category:Film series introduced in 1939]]\n[[Category:Animated film series|Count Screwloose]]\n[[Category:MGM cartoon characters]]\n[[Category:Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer animated short films]]\n[[Category:Comics adapted into animated series]]\n[[Category:Fictional counts and countesses|Screwloose]]\n[[Category:Fictional American people|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with mental disorders|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with dwarfism|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Gag-a-day comics]]\n[[Category:American comics characters|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Male characters in comics|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1929|Screwloose, Count]]\n[[Category:Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer cartoon studio film series]]\n\n{{animation-char-stub}}{{King Features Syndicate Comics}}\n{{Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer Cartoons}}"
