        "title": "The Goodies – Almost Live",
        "content": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2022}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| series       = [[The Goodies (TV series)|The Goodies]]\n| image        =\n| caption      = \n| series_no    = 6\n| episode      = 7\n| director     = [[Jim Franklin (director)|Jim Franklin]]\n| writer       = \n| production   = \n| airdate      = {{Start date|1976|11|02|df=yes}}\n| length       = \n| guests       = '''Musical director''':\n* [[Dave MacRae]]\n'''Musicians''': \n* [[Ron Aspery]]\n* Simon Burns\n* [[Paul Keogh]]\n* [[Richie Hitchcock]]\n* [[Juicy Lucy (band)|Chris Mercer]]\n* [[Barry Morgan (musician)|Barry Morgan]]\n* [[Brian Odges]]\n* [[Alan Parker (musician)|Alan Parker]]\n* [[Graham Prestcott]]\n* Chris Rae\n'''Backing vocals''':\n* [[Jacquie Sullivan]]\n* [[Joy Yates]]\n| prev         = [[2001 & A Bit]]\n| next         = [[Alternative Roots]]\n| episode_list = List of The Goodies episodes \n}}\n\n\"'''The Goodies – Almost Live'''\" is an episode of the [[Great Britain|British]] [[comedy]] television series ''[[The Goodies (TV series)|The Goodies]]''.\n\nThis episode, which takes the form of a pop concert, is also known as \"'''The Goodies in Concert'''\".{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}}\n\nThe Goodies also appear as \"Pan's Grannies\".\n\nWritten by [[The Goodies]], with songs and music by Bill Oddie.\n\n==Songs==\nThe songs, featured in the show (in chronological order), are:\n\n{| style=\"margin:auto;\"  class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Song title|| Announced / <br />Introduced by|| Sung by <br />(Goodies' singers mentioned only)|| Notes\n|- \n| '''The Goodies Theme''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |Graeme|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)|| Series 6 to 8 theme.\n|-\n| '''Please Let Us Play'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Tim, Bill and Graeme|| From ''[[The New Goodies LP]]''.\n|-\n| '''Good Ole Country Music'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Graeme as a 'Cowboy' <br />(Dog and Chicken sounds: courtesy of Bill)|| From ''[[The New Goodies LP]]'' <br />and later released on the B-side of ''Bounce''.\n|-\n| '''Cactus in my Y-Fronts'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Graeme|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Tim as the 'Midnight Cowperson' <br />(accompanied by Bill and Graeme)|| Originally written for ''[[I'm Sorry, I'll Read That Again]]'' <br />and included on ''[[Nothing to Do with Us]]''.\n|-\n| '''Poor Old Soul''' and '''Funky Chicken'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill, Graeme and Tim||\n|-\n| '''[[Funky Gibbon]]'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill, Graeme and Tim|| Released as a single in 1975 and included <br />on ''[[The New Goodies LP]]''.\n|-\n| '''Sick Man Blues''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |Graeme|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill and Tim <br />(Graeme hands out paper bags to audience)|| Originally written for ''[[I'm Sorry, I'll Read That Again]]''.\n|-\n| '''[[The Inbetweenies]]'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)|| Released as a single in 1974.\n|-\n| '''Black Pudding Bertha''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)|| Released as a single the previous year.\n|-\n| '''[[Nappy Love]]''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill <br />(accompanied by Tim and Graeme <br />&mdash; and their hand puppets)|| Originally written for ''[[I'm Sorry, I'll Read That Again]]''. <br />Released as a single in 1975 and included <br />on ''[[The New Goodies LP]]''.\n|-\n| '''Bounce'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Tim|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)|| From \"[[The Goodies Rule – O.K.?]]\" <br />and released as a single earlier in 1976.\n|-\n| '''The Last Chance Dance''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (Tim demonstrates the song with a girl)|| Released on the B-side of <br />''[[Make a Daft Noise for Christmas]]'' in 1975.\n|-\n| '''[[Wild Thing (The Troggs song)|Wild Thing]]''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)|| Released on the B-side of ''[[Nappy Love]]'', <br />included on ''[[The New Goodies LP]]'' <br />and used in \"[[The Goodies Rule – O.K.?]]\".\n|-\n| '''The Goodies Theme''' || style=\"text-align:center;\" |&mdash;|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |Bill (accompanied by Tim and Graeme)||\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n* \"''The Complete Goodies''\" &mdash; Robert Ross, B T Batsford, London, 2000\n* \"''The Goodies Rule OK''\" &mdash; Robert Ross, Carlton Books Ltd, Sydney, 2006\n* \"''The Goodies Episode Summaries''\" &mdash; Brett Allender\n* \"''The Goodies &mdash; Fact File''\" &mdash; Matthew K. Sharp\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb episode|id=0591037|episode=The Goodies &ndash; Almost Live}}\n\n{{The Goodies episodes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goodies - Almost Live, The}}\n[[Category:The Goodies series 6 episodes]]\n[[Category:1976 British television episodes]]"
