        "title": "Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs (Ethiopia)",
        "content": "{{Use American English|date=January 2021}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2021}}\n{{short description|Ethiopian government department}}\n{{Infobox ministry\n| name = Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs\n| native_name = {{lang|am|የሠራተኛና ማህበራዊ ጉዳይ ሚኒስቴር}}\n| seal = Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs (Ethiopia).png\n| logo = \n| formed = {{start date and age|1957|08|12|df=yes}}\n| jurisdiction = Ethiopia\n| headquarters = [[Addis Ababa]], Ethiopia\n| employees = \n| budget = \n| minister1_name = [[Ergoge Tesfaye]]\n| chief1_name = \n| chief1_position = \n| chief2_name = \n| chief2_position = \n| chief3_name = \n| chief3_position = \n| chief4_name = \n| chief4_position = \n| chief5_name = \n| chief5_position = \n| chief6_name = \n| chief6_position = \n| chief7_name = \n| chief7_position = \n| chief8_name = \n| chief8_position = \n| chief9_name = \n| chief9_position = \n| parent_department = \n| website = {{url|https://www.eservices.gov.et/topic/subtopic/2}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs''' ({{langx|am|የሠራተኛና ማህበራዊ ጉዳይ ሚኒስቴር}}) is the [[Ethiopian government]] department established in 1957. Until the ministry got its current name in 1977, it was called the Ministry of Community Development, then the Ministry of Community Development and Social Affairs.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |last= |first= |date= |title=Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs (Ethiopia) {{!}} Devex |url=https://www.devex.com/organizations/ministry-of-labor-and-social-affairs-ethiopia-133925 |archive-url= |archive-date= |access-date=29 January 2021 |website=www.devex.com}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title=Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs|url=https://investin.et/resource-map/ministry-of-labor-and-social-affairs/|access-date=2021-01-29|website=iportal|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\nThe Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs was established in 1957 by Proclamation 15 as the Ministry of Community Development during the reign of [[Haile Selassie]], and this name stayed for nearly a [[decade]], after which it was renamed to the Ministry of Community Development and Social Affairs in 1966 by Proclamation 46.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 1977, during the derg [[regime]], the ministry was named the Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" /> It is under the leadership of [[Ergoge Tesfaye]] since 16 October 2018. The ministry has two main sections, named ''Labor Affairs'', and ''Social Affairs''; the latter has two directorates, ''Employment and Peaceful Industrial Relation Directorate''<ref>{{Cite web|title=Employment and Peaceful Industrial Relation Directorate General – MoLSA|url=http://www.molsa.gov.et/?page_id=151|access-date=2021-01-29|language=en-US}}</ref> and ''Overseas Employment and Workers Safety Protection Directorate''.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Overseas Employment Directorate General – MoLSA|url=http://www.molsa.gov.et/?page_id=149|access-date=2021-01-29|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== List of ministries ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\nList of ministers for Labor and Social Affairs, and prime minister or emperor and presidents during their minister-ship \n!Number\n!Name\n!From\n!To\n!Prime minister/Emperor\n!President\n|-\n|1\n|[[Abdulfetah Abdulahi Hassen]]\n|??\n|??\n|[[Meles Zenawi]]\n|[[Girma Wolde-Giorgis]]\n|-\n|2\n|[[Hirut Woldemariam]]\n|April 2018 \n|16 October 2018\n|[[Abiy Ahmed]]\n|[[Sahle-Work Zewde]]\n|-\n|3\n|[[Ergoge Tesfaye]]\n|16 October 2018\n|present\n|[[Abiy Ahmed]]\n|[[Sahle-Work Zewde]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1957 establishments in Ethiopia]]\n[[Category:Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs of Ethiopia| ]]"
